President Donald J. Trump has announced his intention to nominate Todd M. Harper of Virginia as a Member of the National Credit Union Administration Board. Harper has extensive experience in financial services policy, having served in various government positions. He has worked on initiatives such as the Dodd-Frank Wall Street Reform and Consumer Protection Act and bipartisan legislation on credit union capital rules, terrorism risk insurance, auditing standards, and subprime mortgage lending. Harper holds an M.P.P. from Harvard University's Kennedy School of Government and a B.S. in business analysis from Indiana University's Kelley School of Business.

Additionally, President Trump plans to nominate Ian Paul Steff of Indiana as Assistant Secretary and Director General of the United States and Foreign Commercial Service in the Department of Commerce. Steff currently serves as Deputy Assistant Secretary of Commerce for Manufacturing and previously held positions such as Chief Innovation Officer for the State of Indiana and Executive Vice President of the Indiana Economic Development Corporation. He has also worked in roles related to global policy and technology partnerships. Steff earned his B.A. in International Studies from American University and completed graduate work at the National Defense University and the George Washington University.